-- MPS postpones business plan presentation to June 27
-- 
-- Sat Jun 23, 2012 12:41pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/23/us-montepaschi-board-idUSBRE85M0EX20120623

 

 MILAN  (Reuters) - Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena ( BMPS.MI ), Italy's third biggest lender, said on Saturday a board meeting to approve its new business plan had been postponed by one day to June 26, with the plan now due to be presented to analysts the following day. 
 Monte dei Paschi, which is racing against time to plug a 3.3 billion euros capital shortfall, cited organizational reasons for the delay, without elaborating. (Reporting By Silvia Aloisi)